        </div>
      </td>
      <td valign="top" align="right">
      <div id="CommentBar_3009" style="display:none;">

      
      <span id="FlagComment_3009">
        <a class="iconLink" href="javascript:ajaxLink('FlagComment_3009', '/akira/flagDiscussionComment.do?topicID=3279&commentID=3009')"><img alt="Warning" class="iconLink" src="/images/iconshock/warning_16.gif" border="0">&nbsp;Report Abuse</a>
      </span>
      


            


      </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

      


      Well thought out. Erudite. Reminds me of the 'interactive courtroom simulation' from years ago at Stanford, "Eliminate the process of trial and error, because there's no room for error in a trial." <br/><br/>I love the 'try it out' part; This project marries well with the open source collective knowledge base (govt projects) that I voted for as well...because crowdsourcing is only effective for solution-based thinking when we have an array of lucid scenarios to work with from the get go! 

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


